    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-27T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="582"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/914: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-28T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.40 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese Government requests early information as to whether American Government
                    will advance $1,000,000 Chinese share Siberian Railway loan. I am informed
                    Japanese Minister called at Foreign Office stating his Government would be very
                    glad to furnish this money. Chinese Government hopes American Government will
                        <pb facs="0713" n="611" xml:id="pg_611"/> make the advance as it desires to
                    maintain its independence in matter relating to the Siberian and Chinese Eastern
                    Railway[s]. I beg to request an early and favorable reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
